column16: A service encounter refers to any interaction where you as a customer interacted with a service employee or a service firm, for instance shopping at a retail store, or dining at a restaurant.  In this survey, our aim is to understand customers' awkward service encounters.  To begin, please take a moment to think of a past service encounter which you would label as awkward.  Try and remember exactly what happened and what it was like being in that encounter.
